cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks such as interest point detection and local feature description, which are typically categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of neural networks and metric learning, which are common topics in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of self-supervision, which is a technique commonly used in robotics and autonomous systems, falling under the sub-category of cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on the HPatches dataset, which is a benchmark dataset for image matching and retrieval, falling under the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
